      "actionDate": "2026-05-19",
      "actionDesc": "Introduced in House",
      "text": "<p><strong>Homeland Security Capabilities Preservation Reporting Act of 2026</strong></p><p>This bill requires the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to submit a report to Congress every three years (current law requires only one report) regarding urban areas\u2019 security capabilities previously supported with funding from the Urban Area Security Initiative (UASI) and at risk of being reduced or eliminated without additional federal assistance. FEMA\u2019s UASI grants assist designated high-risk urban areas with developing and sustaining capabilities to prevent, prepare for, protect against, and respond to acts of terrorism.</p><p>Each report must contain a proposal for&nbsp;FEMA to provide financial assistance for at least three consecutive years to urban areas previously receiving UASI funds to allow them to transition to other funding sources to preserve their security capabilities.</p>",
      "updateDate": "2026-07-08T15:08:21Z",
      "versionCode": "00"
    }
  ]
